section.section:
Before the Department may introduce a nonnative oyster into State waters or issue a permit to another person for an introduction, the Department shall:
Subject to § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, submit a report to the General Assembly demonstrating that the Department has met the requirements of paragraph (1) of this subsection;
Conduct public hearings regarding the Department's decision to introduce or to issue a permit to introduce a nonnative oyster into State waters;
For at least 30 days following the last public hearing conducted under item (ii) of this paragraph, receive written public comments on the Department's decision to introduce or to issue a permit to introduce; and
Issue and publish a final decision, including a full scientific rationale for the final decision, a summary of oral and written comments received under items (ii) and (iii) of this paragraph, and the Department's response to these comments, in the Maryland Register; and
Publish the final decision, including all accompanying documentation under item 1 of this item, on the Department's website.
